<headline>Special Weather Statement issued December 16 at 6:52AM CST  by NWS Amarillo</headline>
<description>...A band of snow continues to move south across portions of the
Texas Panhandle...
At 6:50 AM, a main band of snow from Dumas to Borger to Pampa is
moving southeast. Light snowfall accumulations up to an inch, with
locally higher amounts are possible. Reduced visibilities along
with snow covered roadways have already been reported throughout
the early morning hours. These bands of snow may impact travel on
I-40 and I-27. Please use caution if traveling.</description>
